{
  "texts": [
    "Blockchain can be characterized as a growing collection of records in which cryptographically secured structures known as blocks are in the form of a linked list.The Genesis is the first link in the chain (formation block).",
    "Only the Genesis block does not make reference to the previous block digest.",
    "Depending on the use case for the blockchain, several block designs are used.",
    "The blocks on the Ethereum blockchain are distinct from those on the Bitcoin blockchain [10].",
    "The sizes and types of information that blocks can hold will vary depending on how the system is constructed."
  ]
}